HEADWORD: Dispeed
<hw>Dis*peed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>speed</ets>.]</ety> <def>To send off with speed;
to dispatch.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Knolles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then they <qex>dispeeded</qex> themselves of the Cid and of their
mother-in-law, Do⟦ntil⟧a Ximena.</q> <rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dispel</ent>⟦br⟧
